<!-- level 3 - spades, diamonds, clubs -->
<body>
<diagram>
     <hand seat="N" sp="AK843" he="T43" di="A5" cl="Q82"/>
<hand seat="W" sp="JT6" he="AQ982" di="JT4" cl="73"/>
                   <hand seat="E" sp="975" he="K5" di="986" cl="AKJ54"/>
     <hand seat="S" sp="Q2" he="J76" di="KQ732" cl="T96"/>
</diagram>
<p>
This is a typical "six plus promotion" deal.
</p><p>
If North/South declare diamonds
or spades, the defense takes three hearts, three clubs, and on the fourth
club, West ruffs high, promoting a trump in East's hand.
</p><p>
This is essentially a trivial variation of various of our "cooked"
examples in the introduction.
</p></body>
